  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "These are now the chief of their fathers, and this is the genealogy of them,.... Which follows from hence to the end of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 8:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that went up with me from Babylon; with Ezra the priest and scribe, the writer of this book: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in the reign of Artaxerxes the king; that is, Darius Hystaspis, in the seventh year of his reign, see Ezra 7:1, though many think Artaxerxes Longimanus is meant. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "in the reign of Artaxerxes the king; that is, Darius Hystaspis, in the seventh year of his reign, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
